Assistant to the President for National Security Affairs Jake Sullivan hosted Israeli National Security Advisor Tzachi Hanegbi, Minister of Strategic Affairs Ron Dermer, and a senior Israeli delegation at the White House. They discussed their concerns about Iran's nuclear program and pledged to enhance coordination to prevent Iran from acquiring a nuclear weapon. They also reviewed recent joint military exercises and welcomed Secretary of Defense Lloyd Austin's upcoming visit to Israel. The officials also discussed efforts to deepen Israel's integration into the Middle East region through initiatives like the Abraham Accords and the Negev Forum. Mr. Sullivan reiterated President Biden's commitment to Israel's security as expressed in the Jerusalem U.S.-Israel Strategic Partnership Joint Declaration.